\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (21:1\endash 7) }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Introduction}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 : at last the great day came: the promised son was born. The hope and longing were finally realized. It had been twenty-five years since God had given Abraham the promise of a son, twenty-five long years. Now, the waiting was over. Sarah bore Abraham a son, the promised son, the son from whom kings and nations were to be born and from whom the Savior of the world was to come. God always fulfills His promises. He fulfilled His promise to Abraham, and He will fulfill His promises to us. This is the subject of this great chapter: }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 Abraham Saw the Promised Son Isaac Born: Rewarded Faith\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 How God Fulfills His Promises}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , 21:1\endash 7.}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 1.\tab To prove Himself, His Word and power: He has the power to do exactly as He has promised (vv. 1\endash 2).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 2.\tab To stir obedience and faithfulness to God (vv. 3\endash 5).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 3.\tab To stir joy and rejoicing over God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s power (vv. 6\endash 7).\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge21.1-7&off=1314&ctx=on+in+his+old+age.%0a%0a~O.+Abraham+Saw+the+P"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 115). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
