\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs32\b1\i0 1}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  (21:1\endash 2) }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Word of God\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 Promises Of God\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 Isaac}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 : How does God fulfill His promises? He proves Himself, His Word and power. God uses His power to do exactly as He has promised. God kept His Word. Note how the Word of God is stressed. God had promised a son to Abraham and Sarah, and He gave them a son. He did exactly what He had promised He would do.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Note another fact as well: the son was born in Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s \u8220\'93old age,\u8221\'94 at the very time appointed or set by God. The birth was a miracle. Abraham and Sarah were both }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 too old}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  to bear children. They were well beyond childbearing years, but God miraculously quickened\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 made alive, rejuvenated\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 their bodies so that they could bear a child. In fact, the very time for the birth was set by God, and the son was born at the very time God had appointed. The birth was controlled by God from start to finish, controlled by His power. God had the power to prove Himself, to fulfill His promise, His Word, to do exactly as He had promised.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . God keeps His Word, His promises, but God sometimes delays His promises just as He did with Abraham. We often need to grow in our faith \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \bullet \tab to learn more endurance and hardness}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \bullet \tab to become stronger and more determined}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \bullet \tab to learn to trust and hope more in God}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \bullet \tab to pray and fellowship more with God}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 There are a multitude of reasons why God may not immediately fulfill His promises in our lives. But two facts are always true:}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (1)\tab God is faithful to His promises. God will always do exactly what He promises He will do. He may delay for a while in order to strengthen us or to teach us some lesson. But God is faithful; He will prove Himself and fulfill His promises to us.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93God is faithful, by whom ye were called unto the fellowship of his Son Jesus Christ our Lord\u8221\'94 (1 Co. 1:9)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93But the Lord is faithful, who shall stablish you, and keep you from evil\u8221\'94 (2 Th. 3:3)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93If we believe not, yet he abideth faithful: he cannot deny himself\u8221\'94 (2 Ti. 2:13)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Let us hold fast the profession of our faith without wavering; for he is faithful that promised\u8221\'94 (He. 10:23)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (2)\tab God is powerful enough to keep His promises. He has the power to do exactly what He says He will do, the power to fulfill His promises in our lives.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93But Jesus beheld [them], and said unto them, With men this is impossible; but with God all things are possible\u8221\'94 (Mt. 19:26)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93For with God nothing shall be impossible\u8221\'94 (Lu. 1:37)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Now to him that is of power to stablish you according to my gospel, and the preaching of Jesus Christ, according to the revelation of the mystery, which was kept secret since the world began\u8221\'94 (Ro. 16:25)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Now unto him that is able to do exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that worketh in us\u8221\'94 (Ep. 3:20)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Is any thing too hard for the }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0\scaps Lord}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 ?\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8221\'94 (Ge. 18:14)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93I know that thou canst do every thing, and that no thought can be withholden from thee\u8221\'94 (Jb. 42:2)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Thought 2}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Abraham and Sarah had to wait twenty-five years to receive the promise of God. Imagine! Twenty-five years. How impatient we so often become before God.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93That ye be not slothful, but followers of them who through faith and patience inherit the promises\u8221\'94 (He. 6:12)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93And so, after he [Abraham] had patiently endured, he obtained the promise\u8221\'94 (He. 6:15)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93For ye have need of patience, that, after ye have done the will of God, ye might receive the promise\u8221\'94 (He. 10:36)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge21.1-2&off=0&ctx=%E2%80%99s+power+(vv.+6%E2%80%937).%0a~1+(21:1%E2%80%932)+Word+of+G"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, pp. 115\endash 116). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
