\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs32\b1\i0 2}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  (21:3\endash 5) }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Obedience\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 Isaac\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 Circumcision}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 : How does God fulfill His promises? He stirs obedience and faithfulness to God. Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s joy can just be imagined. Remember: when God first told Abraham that the time had finally come, the son was now to be born, Abraham fell on his face in worship (Ge. 17:17). He was so full of joy that he burst forth in laughter, a laughter of faith. God was so pleased with this experience of worship and joy that He instructed Abraham to memorialize the event forever in the name of the child. The name }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 Isaac}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  means \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93he laughs,\u8221\'94 \u8220\'93he joys.\u8221\'94 The long wait for a son\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 twenty-five years\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 was over. The son was born. Abraham\u8217\'92s joy must have broken loose in a praise and worship of God beyond expression. But note: it is not Abraham\u8217\'92s joy that is stressed in these verses; in fact, his joy is not even mentioned. What is the focus? Abraham\u8217\'92s }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 obedience to God}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . This is very significant, for God would not have fulfilled His promise to Abraham if Abraham had not been an obedient follower of God. Abraham obeyed God all throughout his life, not perfectly, but consistently and diligently. Therefore, God was able to fulfill His promises in the life of Abraham. Note how clearly Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s obedience is pictured, even at the birth of his son.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab He named his son Isaac. This was in }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 obedience to God}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . God had long before told Abraham to name his son Isaac (Ge. 17:19).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab He circumcised Isaac when the baby was eight days old. This, too, was in }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 obedience to God}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . God had instituted the ritual of circumcision with Abraham some years before (Ge. 17:10\endash 14).}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Note another fact that is stressed: the miracle of the birth (v. 5). Abraham recognized his dependence upon God: the birth was a miracle. He was 100 years old, well beyond childbearing years. The son was not due to him but to God. God and God alone had given him a son. He was totally dependent upon God, and he owed this blessing\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the blessing of his son\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to God and God alone.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . We must obey God in order to receive the promises of God. This does not mean that we must be perfect before God can pour out His promises upon us. But it does mean that we have to do what Abraham did: believe God and diligently seek to follow God. It means that we set our hearts upon God, that we seek first the kingdom of God and His righteousness, that we diligently seek to obey God.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93But seek ye first the kingdom of God, and his righteousness; and all these things shall be added unto you\u8221\'94 (Mt. 6:33)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Not every one that saith unto me, Lord, Lord, shall enter into the kingdom of heaven; but he that doeth the will of my Father which is in heaven\u8221\'94 (Mt. 7:21)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge21.3-5&off=0&ctx=+crown%E2%80%9D+(Re.+3:11).%0a~2+(21:3%E2%80%935)+Obedience"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 116). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Thought 2}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . God fulfills His promises, always fulfills them.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (1)\tab God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promises never fail.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Blessed be the }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0\scaps Lord}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 , that hath given rest unto his people Israel, according to all that he promised: there hath not failed one word of all his good promise, which he promised by the hand of Moses his servant\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8221\'94 (1 K. 8:56)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (2)\tab God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promises are guaranteed because of His omnipotent, unlimited power.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93He staggered not at the promise of God through unbelief; but was strong in faith, giving glory to God; and being fully persuaded that, what he had promised, he was able also to perform\u8221\'94 (Ro. 4:20\endash 21)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Now unto him that is able to do exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that worketh in us\u8221\'94 (Ep. 3:20)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93For with God nothing shall be impossible\u8221\'94 (Lu. 1:37)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Is any thing too hard for the }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0\scaps Lord}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 ?\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8221\'94 (Ge. 18:14)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (3)\tab God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promises are great and precious.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Whereby are given unto us exceeding great and precious promises: that by these ye might be partakers of the divine nature, having escaped the corruption that is in the world through lust\u8221\'94 (2 Pe. 1:4)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (4)\tab God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promises have one great purpose: to give us eternal life.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93And this is the promise that he hath promised us, even eternal life\u8221\'94 (1 Jn. 2:25)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (5)\tab God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promises are based upon faith.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Jesus said unto him, If thou canst believe, all things [are] possible to him that believeth\u8221\'94 (Mk. 9:23)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93And the Lord said, If ye had faith as a grain of mustard seed, ye might say unto this sycamine tree, Be thou plucked up by the root, and be thou planted in the sea; and it should obey you\u8221\'94 (Lu. 17:6)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge21.6-7&off=6804&ctx=+and+demonstrated.1%0a~Thought+2.+God+fulfi"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, pp. 118\endash 119). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
