\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-720\sb360\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs28\b1 P.}{\f0\fs28 \tab }{\f0\fs28\b1 Abraham Sent Away Hagar and Ishmael, the Slavewoman and Her Son: Conquering Faith\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 Confronting and Overcoming Conflict, 21:8\endash 21}
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (21:8\endash 21) }{\f0\fs24\b1 Introduction}{\f0\fs24 : conflict is always destructive and painful. Conflict destroys }{\f0\fs24\i1 peace}{\f0\fs24  and security, the peace and security \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab of hearts}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab of communities}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab of families}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab of schools}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab of work}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab of nations}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Conflict is painful: it hurts, sometimes mildly, sometimes dangerously. Conflict can range from bumping heads over some issue to conflict and war. It can range from a small disagreement over to locking horns and being divorced from one another. Conflict can arouse a small sense of uneasiness within us or it can rip us apart.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 But note this: we can use conflict to arouse us and stir us to move on and achieve more, or we can allow conflict to destroy us. This is what this passage is all about: confronting and conquering conflict. This is a most interesting story: }{\f0\fs24\i1 Abraham Sent Away Hagar and Ishmael, the Slavewoman and Her Son: Conquering Faith\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 Confronting and Conquering Conflict}{\f0\fs24 , 21:8\endash 21.}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 1.\tab The nature of the conflict: much attention was being showered on Isaac (vv. 8\endash 11).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 2.\tab The answer to the conflict: God (vv. 12\endash 13).}
