\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs32\b1 3}{\f0\fs24  (21:14\endash 16}{\f0\fs24\super b}{\f0\fs24 ) Conflict, Results: there were the results of the conflict. The results were devastating.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 a. There were the broken hearts, the separation, and divorce (v. 14). The conflict was deeply imbedded within Ishmael\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s heart, apparently so imbedded that he would never change. God knew this, so the only way the conflict could ever be resolved was for Ishmael and Hagar, his mother, to be sent away.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 Just picture the scene as Abraham arose early in the morning, taking bread and water to Hagar. There was bound to be tenderness, warmth, love, and brokenness as Abraham set the two leather straps over the shoulders of Hagar and Ishmael and sent them away. The }{\f0\fs24\i1 piercing pain and hurt}{\f0\fs24  must have been almost unbearable.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . The results of conflict are often devastating. Many have had their hearts broken because of conflict, conflict that led to \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab separation}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab divorce}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab the loss of a loved one}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 b. There was the wandering about, being lost, not knowing where to go nor what to do next (v. 14}{\f0\fs24\super b}{\f0\fs24 ). Scripture does not say where Hagar was heading, but she was probably traveling back home to Egypt (Ge. 16:1). For some reason, she lost her way and began to wander all about. She was at a loss, not knowing where to go or what to do next, all because of the conflict.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . Note how Hagar\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s experience pictures the experience of so many persons. So many are wandering about in the world, lost, not knowing where to go or what to do next\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 all because some conflict led to \u8230\'85}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab separation}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab divorce}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab the loss of a loved one}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 So many persons are lost out in the desert of the world, all alone or else with no one but a child. Just think of the single mothers and fathers, the heavy pressure of raising children all alone. The loneliness and desperation of the situation are often almost unbearable.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 c. There was the exhaustion, hopelessness, and threat of death (vv. 15\endash 16). Hagar and Ishmael used up all their provisions. There was no more bread and not even any more water left. They were so exhausted that they could go no farther. Note that Ishmael, the sixteen or seventeen year old young man, had apparently fainted from thirst and exhaustion. Hagar pulled him over under a bush and went off and sat down about a bow shot away. There was no more hope: the situation was now beyond repair; Hagar could do no more. She just could not bear watching him die.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . Think of the people all over the world who \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab are totally exhausted}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab have no food or water}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab are hopeless}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab face the threat of death}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Why? All because of conflict, the conflict that led to separation, divorce, war, or some other devastating result. The results of conflict are destructive, unending in the toll they take upon human life.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge21.14-16b&off=0&ctx=just+as+Abraham+did%0a~3+(21:14%E2%80%9316%EF%BB%BFb)+Confl"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, pp. 122\endash 123). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
